                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-1578" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1578" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1578" type="surname" value="PUDDICOMBE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-1578" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS PUDDICOMBE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the newspaper business, and live in Bridge-house-place, Newington. The prisoner used to carry out news<lb></lb>papers for me—last Wednesday evening I was in the shop, and was called to the parlour, and while I was there I heard a noise—I went out, and he had been at the till, and the till dropped down—it was inside the counter—he was in the shop, but on the other side, when I went away—I said, "John, have you been at my till? "—he said, "Yes"—I said, "Have you ever been there before? "—he said, "Yes, five times"—I asked what he had taken out then—he pulled out 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from his pocket, and said that was it—he had been with me a year and a half, and I had a good opinion of him.</p>
